@NODE Intro "bSP rEASON - sET a rEASON fOR usE wITH kEWLPAGE 2.5+"
----------[ ˇNTRODUCTION ]--------------------------------------------------

Welcome to BSP-Reason!  This program will allow to set a reason for not
being in, when used in conjuction with KewlPage 2.5 + by Steve Clack.

KewlPage x.x will be on Aminet, in the form of KewlPage2x.lha.. so either
check, there, or any good @{"BBS" link BBS} for KewlPage, the best pager
door for MAXs BBS.

BSP-Reason prompts you to enter a reason via a gui, and is VERY simple,
quick, and also "useful".  :-)

I wrote this program cos I was bored.. I hope you get *some* use out of it!

@{b}
Please note!  I actually wrote this program quite a while back, and have
only just got round to releasing it.  Therefore, I haven't actually worked
on it for quite a while, but it has had over 5 months of use, and testing!
Therefore I know it's stable :)
@{ub}



@{"  Back to main menu...  " link MAIN}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Require "rEQUIREMENTS oF bSP rEASON 1.oo"
----------[ rEQUIREMENTS ]--------------------------------------------------

BSP rEASON requires:

MAXs BBS or /X\ Pro
KewlPage 2.5+


@{"  Back to main menu...  " link MAIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE Install "ˇNSTALLING bSP rEASON 1.oo"
----------[ ˇNSTALLATION ]--------------------------------------------------

Installation of BSP Reason is very easy.  Just copy the file to the place of
your choice.. and keep this help guide for handy reference.

It would be a good idea to place BSP rEASON somewhere where you can quickly
access it from Workbench.. althought you can also start the program from the
CLI :)

I select to "Leave Out" bSP rEASON from Workbench - simple! :-)


@{"  Back to main menu...  " link MAIN}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "uSAGE oF bSP rEASON"
----------[ uSAGE oF bSP rEASON ]-------------------------------------------

Usage of BSP rEASON is very easy.  Just start the program, by either
clicking on the icon from Workbench, or from the CLI.  You will be guided
through the program by a set of GUIs.  All you have to do is follow the
instructions through the program in order set your away reason.

The program allows you to store a temporary reason (first gadget), a permanent
reason (second), clear the permanent reason (third), or show the current
reason to be stored (fourth).  You can also quit by selecting "End"


@{b}* You don't even HAVE to use the mouse in this program :)) *@{ub}

You can use the return key, or the mouse to progress through the parts of
the program.. where there is more then one answer, you can use hotkeys :)


@{"  Back to main menu...  " link MAIN}

@ENDNODE

